            <introduction>
                <p>
                   Many families of functions arise as a family of transformations of one or two basic functions, which we can call the <em>parent</em> function of that family. For instance, quadratic functions are all transformations of <m>y = x^2</m>. Now we introduce the family of sinusoidal functions, which have <m>y = \sin(t)</m> and <m>y = \cos(t)</m> as the parent functions. 
                </p>
            </introduction>



